@node "Introduction" "Introduction"
@next "Distribution"
@prev "Main"
@{b}Introduction@{ub}

XFile is one of the most powerful fileeditors for Xenolink 1.90+.
It has allĀthe basic functions the internal fileeditor has, but
has also a lot of specialĀfunctions missing in the internal
fileeditor and other fileditors.

XFile is compact and fully resizeable. It adapts itself to
differentĀfontwidths and fontheights if possible. Works well in
different screenmodes,Āresolutions and enviroments.

XFile has as only file editor full capabilities to @{"testĀandĀview" link "File Information Window Menus" 0}
the files.

XFile supports AppIcon, and will always de-iconify as it was when
you iconfied it (all windows reopen exactly as they were!).

XFile is very user-friendly. You can as an experienced Xenolink
SysOp almostĀuse the programs basic functions at once. You should
however sit down andĀread the documentation carefully before you
decide to use XFile fully out. ItĀhas a lot of minor things you
might find useful.

@endnode

